Set up the performance analysis methods¶

In [3]:
def create_image_tensor(tensorGenerator, setLabel, shuffle=False):
    return tensorGenerator.flow_from_directory(data_folder + '/' + setLabel,                                              
                                        target_size = (img_size, img_size),
                                        color_mode = 'rgb',
                                        batch_size = batch_size,
                                        class_mode = 'categorical',
                                        classes = img_classes,
                                        shuffle = shuffle)

def plot_training_histories(histories, titles, columns=1):
    numPlots = len(histories)
    rows = (numPlots // columns)+1
    plt.figure(figsize = (rows*3, columns*3))
    for i in range(numPlots):
        plt.subplot(rows, columns, i+1)
        plt.title(titles[i])
        plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
        plt.xlabel('Epochs')
        pointCount = len(histories[i].history['accuracy']) + 1
        list_ep = [i for i in range(1, pointCount)]
        plt.plot(list_ep, histories[i].history['accuracy'], ls = '--', label = 'accuracy')
        plt.plot(list_ep, histories[i].history['val_accuracy'], ls = '--', label = 'val_accuracy')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

def plot_mispredictions(trueClasses, predictedClasses, classLabels, dataSet, columns=5):
    mispredicts = []
    for i in range(len(trueClasses)):
        truth = trueClasses[i]
        prediction = predictedClasses[i]
        if trueClasses[i] != predictedClasses[i]:
            mispredicts.append((truth, prediction, i))

    missCount = len(mispredicts)
    rows = (missCount // columns)+1
    plt.figure(figsize = (rows*3, columns*3))
    print(f'\nMisprediction Count:{missCount}\n')
    for i in range(missCount):
            truth, prediction, imgIndex = mispredicts[i]
            plt.subplot(rows, columns, i+1)
            plt.title(f'T:{classLabels[truth]} P:{classLabels[prediction]}', {'color':'red'}, loc='center')
            plt.imshow(PIL.Image.open(dataSet.filepaths[imgIndex]), cmap='gray')
            plt.xticks([])
            plt.yticks([])
    plt.show()

def draw_confusion_matrix(trueLabels, predictedLabels, modelTitle='Model'):
    cm = confusion_matrix(trueLabels, predictedLabels)
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 5))
    plt.title(modelTitle)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot = True,  fmt = '.0f', xticklabels=img_classes, yticklabels=img_classes)
    plt.ylabel('Actual')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.show()

def print_report(trueLabels, predictedLabels):
    indices = [0,1,2,3]
    print(classification_report(trueLabels, predictedLabels, labels=indices, target_names=img_classes))

def augmented_predict(model, inData, num_permutations):
    trueLabels = []
    predictedLabels = []
    test_iter = iter(inData)
    for batchIndex in range(0, len(test_iter)):
        batch = next(test_iter)
        batch_images = batch[0]
        batch_labels = batch[1]
        for imgIndex in range(0, len(batch_images)):
            aug_images = [batch_images[imgIndex]]
            img_label = np.argmax(batch_labels[imgIndex], axis=0)
            for permutationIndex in range(0, num_permutations):
                aug_img = img_augmented_testing_tensor_generator.random_transform (batch_images[imgIndex])
                aug_images.append(aug_img)
            aug_images = np.array(aug_images)
            aug_pred = model.predict_on_batch(aug_images) # make predictions on all images
            aug_pred = np.mean(aug_pred, axis=0) # create the 'average' prediction
            aug_label = np.argmax(aug_pred) # convert the prediction to a label
            predictedLabels.append(aug_label)
            trueLabels.append(img_label)

    return (np.array(trueLabels), np.array(predictedLabels))

Set up methods for creating the various models we wish to test.¶

In [6]:
base_models = [
    (ap.VGG16, ap.vgg16.preprocess_input),
    (ap.VGG19, ap.vgg19.preprocess_input),
    (ap.ResNet50, ap.resnet50.preprocess_input),
    (ap.ResNet50V2, ap.resnet_v2.preprocess_input),
    (ap.EfficientNetB2, ap.resnet_v2.preprocess_input),
    (ap.EfficientNetV2B2, ap.efficientnet_v2.preprocess_input),
]

optimizers = [
    (Adam, {}),
    (SGD, {'momentum':0.9}),
]

def create_hypermodel(hp:kt.HyperParameters):
    #select the model and construct it
    baseIndex = hp.get('base_model_index')
    modelFunc, preprocessFunc = base_models[baseIndex]
    base = modelFunc(include_top=False, input_shape=img_shape)

    input = InputLayer(input_shape=img_shape)
    preprocess = Lambda(lambda x:preprocessFunc(x.output))(input)
    transfer = base(preprocess)

    #select the flatten layer method
    if hp.Boolean('flatten_layer'):
        flatten = Flatten()(transfer)
    else:
        flatten = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(transfer)
    
    #set up the fully connected blocks
    dense = flatten
    for denseIndex in range(hp.Int('dense_block_count', 1, 4)):
        denseBlockParam = f'dense_block{denseIndex}'
        hp.Fixed(denseBlockParam, denseIndex)
        with hp.conditional_scope(denseBlockParam, [denseIndex]):            
            dense = Dense(hp.Int(f'dense_block{denseIndex}_dense', 64, 512, 32), activation='relu')(dense)
            if hp.Boolean(f'dense_block{denseIndex}_dropout'):
                dense = Dropout(0.25)(dense)
            if hp.Boolean(f'dense_block{denseIndex}_batchnormal'):
                dense = BatchNormalization()(dense)

    #add our classification layer and compile the model
    classification = Dense(4, activation='softmax')(dense)
    model = Model(preprocess, classification, name=base.name)

    #select the optimizer method and construction arguments
    optimizerIndex = hp.Int('optimizer_index', 0, len(optimizers)-1)
    optimizer_func, optimizer_args = optimizers[optimizerIndex]    
    
    #select the learning rate and add it to the optimizer arguments
    lr = hp.Float('learning_rate', 1e-4, 1e-2, sampling='log')
    working_optimizer_args = optimizer_args.copy()
    working_optimizer_args['learning_rate'] = lr
    
    #construct the optimizer
    optimizer = optimizer_func(**working_optimizer_args)

    model.compile(loss=categorical_crossentropy, optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model

baseResults = []
for i in range(len(base_models)):
    #instantiate the base model
    params = kt.HyperParameters()
    params.Fixed('base_model_index', i)
    baseModel = create_hypermodel(params)

    #train for a few epochs to get some insight into its performance on our data
    basePredictions = []
    print(f'\nBaseline: {baseModel.name}:\n')
    untunedHistory = baseModel.fit(train_set, validation_data=validation_set, epochs=untuned_epochs)
    basePredictions = baseModel.predict(validation_set)
    baseResults.append((i, untunedHistory, basePredictions))
    print('\n')
    plot_training_histories([untunedHistory], [baseModel.name])

Take the best base models and tune their hyperparameters¶

In [8]:
tuned_results = []
for i in range(min(models_to_keep_pre_tuning, len(baseResults))):
    modelIndex, untunedHistory, basePredictions = baseResults[i]
    modelParams = kt.HyperParameters()
    modelParams.Fixed('base_model_index', modelIndex)

    tuning_val_acc = []
    tuner = kt.BayesianOptimization(create_hypermodel, hyperparameters=modelParams, objective="val_accuracy", beta=3.1, overwrite=True, max_trials=tuning_trials, directory=tuner_log_path, project_name='Capstone')
    get_results = lambda epoch, logs: tuning_val_acc.append(logs['val_accuracy'])
    tuner.search(train_set, validation_data=validation_set, callbacks=[LambdaCallback(on_epoch_end=get_results)] )
    tuned_params = tuner.get_best_hyperparameters(tuning_trials)
    tuning_val_acc.sort(reverse=True)
    for j in range(len(tuning_val_acc)):
        tuned_results.append((tuning_val_acc[j], tuned_params[j]))

#order the results by mean val_accuracy
tuned_results.sort(key=lambda x:x[0], reverse=True)

Train and test the best tuned models¶

In [9]:
modelResults = []
for i in range(min(models_to_keep_post_tuning, len(tuned_results))):
    tuning_accuracy, tuned_parameters = tuned_results[i]

    #instantiate the tuned model
    tunedModel = create_hypermodel(tuned_parameters)
    configurationName = f'{tunedModel.name}-{hash(tunedModel)}'
    checkpointPath = './{0}.h5'.format(configurationName)
   
    #set up the model callbacks to checkpoint progress, capture the best weight configuration for val_accuracy, and potentially save time
    checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(checkpointPath, monitor='val_accuracy', save_best_only=True, mode='max')
    earlyStop = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', mode='max', min_delta=0.005, patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)
    tensorBoard = TensorBoard(tuner_log_path, histogram_freq=5, write_images=True, write_graph=False, write_steps_per_second=True)

    #train the model
    print(f'\nTuned: {configurationName}\n')

    tunedHistory = tunedModel.fit(train_set, validation_data=validation_set, epochs=tuned_epochs, callbacks=[checkpoint, earlyStop, tensorBoard])
    
    #restore the best fit weights for value accuracy
    tunedModel.load_weights(checkpointPath)

    #show a plot of the model's training history for accuracy and value accuracy
    plot_training_histories([tunedHistory], [configurationName])

    #test the model
    aug_labels, aug_predictions = augmented_predict(tunedModel, test_set, 10)
    
    modelResults.append((configurationName, tuned_parameters, tunedModel, tunedHistory, (aug_labels, aug_predictions)))
